---
# Bandit configuration — rules we have reviewed and deliberately accept.
#
# skips: project-wide false-positive rules that arise from legitimate desktop-app
# patterns (subprocess with static arg lists, non-crypto random for UI jitter,
# translator strings containing the word "password", etc.). See notes below.
#
# B105 hardcoded_password_string
#   False positives in Imervue/multi_language/*.py where translator dictionary
#   keys such as "password_label" or values like "Enter password:" trip the
#   heuristic. No actual secrets are stored in source.
# B110 try_except_pass
#   Only two call sites, both intentional "optional metadata / EXIF parse may
#   fail, fall back" patterns that already carry `# noqa: BLE001` suppressions.
# B311 random
#   Used exclusively for UI jitter (brush stroke noise, random-image pick).
#   Never for cryptographic purposes — the `secrets` module is used where
#   security matters (e.g. session tokens — none currently in this repo).
# B403 import_pickle
#   Imported by clip_search.py only for torch model state-dict loading from
#   disk files we wrote ourselves; no untrusted input reaches pickle.load.
# B404 subprocess_import
#   Used solely with static argument lists for trusted OS tools (explorer,
#   xdg-open, osascript, gsettings, pip inside the embedded venv).
# B603 subprocess_without_shell_equals_true
#   All subprocess.* calls pass list arguments with shell=False. Flagged only
#   because any subprocess use is considered suspect at the default LOW level.
# B606 start_process_with_no_shell
#   Single os.startfile site, intentional for the "Reveal in folder" action.
# B607 start_process_with_partial_path
#   "python", "pip", "explorer" are deliberately resolved via PATH because the
#   app needs to work across Windows/macOS/Linux installs.
skips:
  - B105
  - B110
  - B311
  - B403
  - B404
  - B603
  - B606
  - B607
exclude_dirs:
  - tests
